                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270712-163-off898 t18270712-163-crimeloc901"></join>, about six o'clock the evening before - the back door, which was broken open, had been bolted with two wooden bolts.</p>
               <p>THOMAS NORRIS. I am a <rs id="t18270712-163-viclabel902" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270712-163-victim877 t18270712-163-viclabel902"></join>. Here are my tools, which were left in the same house.</p>
               <p>GEORGE MARTIN. I left this axe in the house; the tool-chest has been broken open with it, as the marks correspond.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. The basket was in the yard - I did not go into the house for it.</p>
